You extract structured knowledge from a passage. Read carefully and produce
atomic propositions, each with one or more (subject, predicate, object) triples.
Each triple is tagged with exactly one ontology axis from the list below.

The axis tagging is the most important part. Use it consistently per these
rubrics. All canonical surface forms are lowercase snake_case.

- causal: the triple expresses cause and effect, enablement, or production.
  Test: would Y still happen if X were absent? If no → causal.
  Templates: "X causes Y", "X leads to Y", "X enables Y", "X triggers Y".
  Examples:
    (vector_index, accelerates, ann_search) → causal
    (null_embedding, produces, ora_21560) → causal

- taxonomic: the triple places X within a category or class hierarchy of Y.
  Test: can "X is a kind of Y" replace the predicate? If yes → taxonomic.
  Templates: "X is a kind of Y", "X is a subclass of Y", "X is_a Y".
  Examples:
    (hnsw, is_a, graph_index_algorithm) → taxonomic
    (oracle_23ai, is_a, oracle_database_release) → taxonomic

- temporal: the triple expresses ordering, version introduction, or deprecation.
  Test: is there any causal mechanism implied? If no → temporal.
  Templates: "X precedes Y", "X was introduced in Y", "X was deprecated in Y",
  "X replaces Y".
  Examples:
    (oracle_23ai, introduced_after, oracle_21c) → temporal
    (legacy_xmltype_indexes, deprecated_in, oracle_23ai) → temporal

- definitional: the triple expresses meaning, terminology, or lexical expansion.
  Test: is this an acronym, a synonym, or a "X means Y" relation? If yes → definitional.
  Templates: "X is defined as Y", "X stands for Y", "X means Y", "X refers to Y".
  Examples:
    (hnsw, stands_for, hierarchical_navigable_small_world) → definitional
    (vector_distance, refers_to, similarity_metric_between_vectors) → definitional

- exemplification: the triple provides a concrete instance or illustration.
  Test: is Y a specific example of category X? If yes → exemplification.
  Templates: "X is an example of Y", "X illustrates Y", "an instance of X is Y".
  Examples:
    (dbms_vector, is_example_of, vector_plsql_package) → exemplification
    (cosine, is_example_of, vector_distance_metric) → exemplification

